<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B77164678E8F9D823F4F909" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B77164678E8F9D823F4F909" blockId="7.[136,1452,1490,2093]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B77164678E8F9D826D5F99D" bold="true" box="[189,399,1562,1588]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—The species belongs to sect. 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7716467AB8F9D82437F99D" authorityName="Fryxell" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="de Candolle" box="[749,877,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cordifoliae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7716467AB8F9D82437F99D" box="[749,877,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Cordifoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7716467B29F9D82337F99D" author="Monteiro-Filho, H. C." box="[892,1133,1562,1588]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" refId="ref19920" refString="Monteiro-Filho, H. C. (1936) Monografia da Malvaceae Brasileiras. Fasc. I. O genero Sida. Revisao das especies brasileiras. 1 ª Parte. Chave das especies sul americanas e novidades brasileiras. Ministerio da Agricultura, Departamento Nacional de Producao Vegetal, Servico de Plantas Texteis, Rio de Janeiro, 56 pp." type="book" year="1936">Monteiro-Filho 1936</bibRefCitation>
, Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7716467C8BF9D92244F99D" box="[1246,1310,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">et. al.</emphasis>
2017) 
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7716467D3BF9D827CCF9F1" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
, and is distinguished from the other species in this section in 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7716467B37F9FC2363F9F1" box="[866,1081,1598,1624]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
by its denser stellate trichomes, yellow flowers (sometimes with a red basal spot), and by the shape of leaves, generally ovate or cordiform (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7716467D03F9A02796F909" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@8.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–E. Sida cordifolia. A. Flower. B.Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Abaxial surface of leaf. D. Branch with leaves and schizocarps. E. Branch with leaves, flowers buds and schizocarps. F–J. Sida dubia. F. Flower. G. Adaxial surface of leaf. H. Abaxial surface of leaf. I. Schizocarps and mericarps. J. Branch with leaves, flowers and buds. K–N. Sida glaziovii. K. Flower. L. Flowers, buds and leaves. M. Branch. N. Buds. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415493/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Figures 3A–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7716467882F944265DF909" box="[215,263,1670,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">14F</figureCitation>
). It is one of the most polymorphic species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7716467B2BF94423F0F909" authority="(Brandao et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Brandao" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[894,1194,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7716467B2BF94424EAF909" box="[894,944,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Sida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7716467BEAF94423F8F909" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[959,1186,1670,1696]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7716467C73F9452305F909" box="[1062,1119,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B77164678E8F9682672F8D1" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B77164678E8F9682672F8D1" blockId="7.[136,1452,1490,2093]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B77164678E8F9682595F96D" bold="true" box="[189,719,1706,1732]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Distribution, habitat and conservation satus:</emphasis>
—This species is widely distributed in pantropical and subtropical regions (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B77164678BDF90C2621F940" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[232,379,1742,1769]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" pagination="62 - 91" refId="ref18743" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1985) The North and Central American species of Sida. Sida, Contributions to Botany 11: 62 - 91." type="journal article" year="1985">Fryxell 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B77164679D1F90C253BF941" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[388,609,1742,1768]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B77164679BCF90D2545F941" box="[489,543,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
), and, therefore, is here considered Least Concern (LC). In 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7716467CB9F90C2269F941" box="[1260,1331,1742,1768]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B77164678FDF9302611F8A5" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[168,331,1778,1804]" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, the species occurs throughout the country. In the present work, we confirm the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7716467DC3F93127AFF899" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordifolia">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7716467DC3F93127AFF899" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">S. cordifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the states of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B77164679FEF8D4250AF899" box="[427,592,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7716467ADCF8D4243BF899" box="[649,865,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
. In the latter state, the species occurs in Inland submontane grassland, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B771646793FF8F8269EF8FD" box="[362,452,1850,1876]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aristida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B771646793FF8F8269EF8FD" box="[362,452,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Aristida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grassland, Sandy grassland and in Coastal grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7716467C7FF8F823D7F8FD" box="[1066,1165,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[262,1350,253,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[199,1389,190,1947]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Sida anomala, S. cerradoensis, S. confusa, S. cordifolia, S. dubia, S. farroupilhensis and S. lonchitis in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415491/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="112">Figure 2</figureCitation>
), also growing in ruderal environments.
